export const DESIGN_INTELLIGENCE = "# KENT WEB DESIGN — DESIGN INTELLIGENCE (skills distilled to text)\n> The design *know-how* from our `/web-design`, `/ui-ux-pro-max` and `/ui-styling` skills, written out so the portal build (which can't run the skills) still gets it. Read alongside `MASTER-BUILD-PROMPT.md` + `DESIGN-REFERENCES.md`.\n\n## A. The proven section library (build from these, top to bottom)\nA premium local-service site is assembled from these battle-tested sections — not invented from scratch each time:\n- **Sticky header** — logo left, **absolutely-centred nav**, inverse-colour phone/CTA button right, hamburger on mobile, `backdrop-filter:blur`.\n- **Hero** — real photo (or rich CSS scene) with a **gradient veil overlay** (NOT a cut-out subject on a flat gradient), a badge (★ rating / years established), a keyword-led H1 with ONE accent word, a benefit subhead, **2 CTAs (primary + Call Now)**, and 3 quick stats.\n- **Trust strip** — 3–4 icon + label reassurances (insured, 24/7, no hidden fees, guaranteed).\n- **Keyword/audience strip** — a wrapping list of use-cases/services; doubles as an SEO keyword surface (add an `sr-only` H2).\n- **Service cards** — icon/image, tag, title, one benefit line, block CTA. One card per real service.\n- **Numbered step timeline** (\"how it works\") — big gradient number markers + connector line; each step a keyword H2, body, ✓ checklist. Worth its own page with HowTo schema.\n- **Reviews grid** — REAL reviews only, star row, avatar initial, name + \"Google review\". Pair with a rating badge + Review schema.\n- **FAQ accordion** — categorised, button+panel driven by JS (or `<details>`). Its own page with FAQPage schema.\n- **Guarantees / why-choose-us band** — from the client's real promises.\n- **CTA bands** between sections — don't make people hunt to call/enquire.\n- **Photo footer** — background photo + strong brand gradient overlay (~90%), **white-knockout logo**, link columns, socials, NAP, \"Built by Kent Web Design\" credit.\n- **Floating WhatsApp FAB** — only if a WhatsApp mobile is supplied; `wa.me/<intl>` with a prefilled message.\n- **Page heroes** for inner pages — breadcrumb + H1 + sub.\n\n## B. Design-system tokens (define once, in `:root`)\nDerive the palette **from the client's logo** (sample real colours, don't invent). Then:\n```\n--ink (near-black text) --slate (muted text) --line (borders)\n--bg --soft --soft-2 (section backgrounds) --brand + --brand-700 (one accent → all CTAs)\n--grad: a brand gradient (hero veils, numbered markers, dark sections)\n--shadow-sm / --shadow (soft, diffuse) --r:16px --r-lg:26px --maxw:1200px\n--font (humanist body) --head (display/condensed heading face)\n```\n- **Headings:** distinctive display face — often condensed, can be uppercase, tight line-height. **Body:** humanist sans, line-height 1.6, base 16px min.\n- **One accent colour** does all the CTAs. The gradient carries drama (hero veil, dark bands, number markers).\n- **Premium = space + restraint, not effects.** Generous section padding (~80–96px), `max-width:1200px` container, soft shadows, 16–26px radii.\n\n## C. Font pairings (pick one that complements the logo — don't default to Inter every time)\n| Mood / trade feel | Heading | Body |\n|---|---|---|\n| Bold/strong (builders, roofers, scaffolders) | Bebas Neue *(headlines only)* | Source Sans 3 |\n| Modern professional (most trades, B2B) | Poppins | Open Sans |\n| Geometric modern (agencies, clean brands) | Outfit | Work Sans |\n| Distinctive tech/innovative | Space Grotesk | DM Sans |\n| Premium/elegant (beauty, interiors, clinics) | Playfair Display | Inter |\n| Calm/wellness (spa, health, therapy) | Lora | Raleway |\n| Versatile single-family fallback | Plus Jakarta Sans | Plus Jakarta Sans |\nLoad via Google Fonts with `preconnect` + `display=swap`, limited weights.\n\n## D. Style-per-trade reasoning (match the look to the business)\n- **Trades & local services (roofers, electricians, heating, hire):** Trust & Authority + Minimalism + tasteful depth. Professional/brand colour + neutral base, clear hierarchy, real photos with gradient veils, section transitions on scroll. **Avoid** playful neon, brutalism, and \"AI purple/pink\" gradients — they read cheap/untrustworthy for a trade.\n- **Premium/beauty/interiors:** elegant serif heading, more white space, refined 400–600ms transitions, restrained accent.\n- **Depth techniques that read premium (use with intent):** glassmorphism cards (`backdrop-filter:blur(12–20px)`, translucent white 15–30%, 1px light border), soft aurora/mesh gradient backgrounds (slow 8–12s loops) for a hero, layered shadows. Keep text contrast ≥ 4.5:1 over any of them.\n- **Consistency:** one style across every page. Never mix flat + skeuomorphic randomly.\n\n## E. UX laws (non-negotiable quality checks)\n- **Accessibility:** contrast ≥ 4.5:1 (text), visible focus rings 2–4px, alt text, `aria-label` on icon-only buttons, sequential headings, respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.\n- **Touch:** targets ≥ 44×44px, ≥ 8px apart; primary actions on tap not hover; `touch-action:manipulation`.\n- **Animation:** 150–300ms, easing not linear; **animate `transform`/`opacity`, never `width`/`height`/`top`** (jank); motion must convey meaning, not decorate.\n- **Forms:** visible labels (never placeholder-only), error message next to the field, helper text, honeypot spam guard, on-page success state.\n- **Icons:** SVG (Heroicons/Lucide style), **never emoji as icons**.\n- **Performance:** WebP/AVIF, `width`/`height` or `aspect-ratio` on every image (CLS < 0.1), lazy-load below fold, `font-display:swap`, critical CSS first.\n\n## F. Craft rules that separate premium from amateur\n- Hero/footer readability = a **gradient overlay on the photo**, never darkening the image itself or cutting the subject onto a flat gradient.\n- **White-knockout logo** on dark backgrounds (punch interior detail to transparent — don't flat-fill to a white blob).\n- Set heading colour explicitly on hero headings (a global `h1{color}` can override and break them).\n- One source of truth for facts (prices, phone, hours) — identical on every page.\n\n## G. Anti-patterns (never ship)\n- Fabricated reviews/ratings/stats/accreditations. Gray-on-gray text. Raw hex in components instead of tokens.\n- Emoji icons. Doubled-up sections saying the same thing (a mini stepper AND a full timeline). Text below 12px in body.\n- Hover-only interactions. Instant (0ms) state changes. Preloaders. Edge-to-edge text with no padding.\n- Neon/brutalist/\"AI gradient\" looks on a conservative local trade.\n";
